The Western Cape is gearing up for heavy rains and gale-force winds over the next few days. eNCA's Monique Mortlock shares more details on this. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape is gearing up for heavy rains and gale-force winds over the next few days. Emergency services are on high alert for possible localised flooding especially in townships without proper drainage systems. READ: Thundershowers, heavy rains expected in Western Cape Two people died in flood waters in Bonnievale on Wednesday. Areas impacted include Struisbaai and parts of the Winelands.